Sonko should be made to pay for his confessed crimes 
MYLES LEO
Kenya has its problems. And they are many.
But the biggest economy in the East African region finds a way for her citizens and visitors to relieve their stress, comically. The country’s political scene is a comedy theatre. One of the main actors in the comedy is Gideon Kioko Mbuvi Sonko.



