But Sonko did not stop.
Speaking in Dagoretti South last Sunday, Sonko claimed he and Interior Principal Secretary Karanja Kibicho were involved in burning of vehicles, to paint ODM in bad light during the 2017 electoral period.
 “We are now seeing the deep state burning cars to paint hustlers in bad light. I want to confess and say this; in 2017 when ODM was holding demonstrations in Nairobi, Kibicho, I and other members of the deep state printed ODM T-shirts and bought old second hand vehicles and burnt then along Ngong road to make it appear like the party was behind the move,” Sonko told a cheering crowd at an event.
PS Kibicho refuted the claims by Sonko. And now the PS is breathing fire.
Sonko has also claimed that his life and that of the Deputy President William Ruto are in danger because of their political standing.
It is time the country stopped playing games with national security. Because Sonko is adamant that he has evidence to support his claims, he must be compelled to provide them now. The allegations he is making are too grave to be dismissed.
Having confessed that he was involved in a criminal act, the former governor should be made ‘to help police with investigations” even before Mr Kibicho and company file their own complaints.



